cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

This paper focuses on computation offloading in mobile edge networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also incorporates machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI) to predict metrics useful for computation offloading. Finally, the paper explores the viability of using Knowledge-Defined Networking (KDN) to make intelligent predictions, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
